comment.author: 13935339@N05
comment._content:
'33SG' denotes the 33rd Service Group, the ground support component of the 56th Fighter Group. 

On 6 March 1944, returning from flying support for the 8th AF's raid on Berlin, LT Adam J. Wisniewski rode through this landing accident at Halesworth while flying P-47D serial 42-75575 (coded UN-N); he was fatigued but unhurt.
